Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, season chicken with salt and pepper, if desired. Place on unheated rack of broiler pan. Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat 6 to 7 minutes per side. Meanwhile, combine undrained tomatoes, broth and peppers in medium saucepan. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. Divide hot pasta among 4 plates. Slice chicken and arrange over pasta. Top with sauce. Garnish with rosemary, if desired.